(Description)
You are given an array prices where prices[i] is the price of a given stock on the ith day.
You want to maximize your profit by choosing a single day to buy one stock and choosing a different day in the future to sell that stock.
Return the maximum profit you can achieve from this transaction. If you cannot achieve any profit, return 0.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        int buyPrice = prices[0];
        int maxProfit = 0;

        for (int price : prices) {
            if (price < buyPrice) {
                buyPrice = price;
            }
            else {
                maxProfit = Math.max(maxProfit, price - buyPrice);
            }
        }

        return maxProfit;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
(Key Point)
- Calculating the most max profit in each position of the given array prices.
Then, if the calculated maxProfit is bigger than last one, replace the value.

To calculate the max profit, for loop was used.
In the loop, it divide into two cases,
1. If the current price is lower than the one that was purchased before, buyprice is replaced by current one.
2. Else, in the case that the current prices is bigger than the buy price, it calculates max profit.
